But it's really those payment rates are remaining quite high, quite elevated. The good news is that plays through in the form of a benefit as it relates to cost of credit, lower losses than expected and now lower reserves as we see releases. But it's really that dynamic of payment rates high, lower loan volumes, average interest earning, in particular, that is putting pressure on that top line.

